TY  - JOUR
TI  - Missing Events in Event Studies
AU  - Gürkaynak, Refet S.
AU  - Kısacıkoğlu, Burçin
AU  - Wright, Jonathan H.
AB  - [Macroeconomic news announcements are elaborate and multidimensional. We consider a framework in which jumps in asset prices around announcements reflect both the response to observed surprises in headline numbers and to latent factors, reflecting other news in the release. Non-headline news, for which there are no expectations surveys, is unobservable to the econometrician but nonetheless elicits a market response. We estimate the model by the Kalman filter, which efficiently combines OLS and heteroskedasticity-based event study estimators in one step. With the inclusion of a single latent surprise factor, essentially all yield curve variance in event windows are explained by news.]
